 Kai Windsor , now 10 with his mother Rachel , started life as a girl -- and knew from the age of three that he had been born into the wrong body .
By four , he refused to wear dresses -- and developed a boyish awkwardness around girls .
Now Kai is set to undergo hormone treatment to stop him developing into a woman .
The number of transgender referrals to the NHS for children under 11 has quadrupled since 2009 .